---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Gomoku"
  description="A fully playable Gomoku board game with AI opponent, built in Java by Alexandros Emmanouilidis. First-year CS coursework with three play modes and JUnit tests."
>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container--narrow">

      <a href="/portfolio" class="back-link">&larr; Portfolio</a>

      <div class="project-header">
        <span class="item-tag">Java · Software · 2026</span>
        <h1>Gomoku</h1>
      </div>

      <div class="project-body">
        <p class="project-lead">
          A fully playable implementation of Gomoku - the Japanese five-in-a-row strategy
          game - built from scratch in Java.
        </p>

        <p>
          Three play modes: Human vs Human, Human vs Computer, and Computer vs Computer.
          The computer opponent uses a strategy-based AI - evaluating board positions to
          make competitive moves rather than playing randomly. The board renders to the
          terminal, and a full suite of JUnit unit tests covers the core game logic.
        </p>

        <div class="spec-grid">
          <div class="spec-item">
            <span class="spec-label">Language</span>
            <span class="spec-value">Java</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-item">
            <span class="spec-label">Context</span>
            <span class="spec-value">Year 1 university coursework, Semester 2</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-item">
            <span class="spec-label">Year</span>
            <span class="spec-value">2026</span>
          </div>
          <div class="spec-item">
            <span class="spec-label">Testing</span>
            <span class="spec-value">JUnit unit tests</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="section-subhead">What it demonstrates</h2>
        <ul class="feature-list">
          <li>Object-oriented design with clear separation of concerns</li>
          <li>AI logic - position evaluation and strategic decision-making</li>
          <li>Unit testing with JUnit</li>
          <li>Clean code documentation (Javadoc)</li>
          <li>Three-mode game loop with input validation</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="honest-note">
          <span class="note-label">Honest framing</span>
          <p>This is first-year coursework, not a commercial project. It's here because it
          is complete, functional, and demonstrates structured thinking at the start of a
          CS degree. As more substantial work accumulates, it will move down the list.</p>
        </div>

        <a
          href="https://github.com/Zap-Dude/gomoku"
          class="btn btn--ghost source-link"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
        >
          View source on GitHub &rarr;
        </a>
      </div>

      <hr class="divider" />

      <div class="project-footer">
        <a href="/portfolio" class="btn btn--ghost">&larr; Back to portfolio</a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .back-link {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    text-decoration: none;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
    transition: color var(--transition);
  }

  .back-link:hover { color: var(--color-accent); }

  .project-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .item-tag {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
  }

  h1 { margin-top: 0; }

  .project-lead {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-style: italic;
    max-width: 56ch;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .spec-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-sm) var(--space-xl);
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    margin-block: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .spec-item {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.2rem;
  }

  .spec-label {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .spec-value {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }

  .section-subhead {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .feature-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .feature-list li {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .feature-list li::before {
    content: '-';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    top: 0.1em;
  }

  .honest-note {
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-border);
    padding: var(--space-md) var(--space-lg);
    border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .note-label {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .honest-note p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    margin: 0;
    max-width: 55ch;
  }

  .source-link {
    display: inline-flex;
  }

  .project-footer {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .spec-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
